## Body Modification Guide

- Treat the body as markdown content stored after the YAML frontmatter.
- Prefer exact-match body replacements when updating checklists or headings so concurrent edits are easier to validate.
- Append new sections instead of rewriting the whole body when you only need to add notes, verification details, or a summary of changes.
- Keep checklist items accurate as work progresses; mark each completed item with `- [x]` as soon as it is done.

## Concurrency Control

- Read the latest ishoo content before editing it.
- Use etags or another current-content check when the CLI supports them so updates fail safely instead of overwriting newer edits.
- If the underlying file changes between read and write, reload the ishoo and reapply the intended edit against the newest content.

## Relationship Model

- `parent`: hierarchy only; use it to group related ishoos under milestones, epics, or larger features.
- `blocking`: IDs of ishoos that this ishoo is actively blocking.
- `blocked_by`: IDs of prerequisites that must finish before this ishoo can move forward.
- Do not infer blocking from parent/child relationships alone; hierarchy and dependency links mean different things.

## Working Rules For Agents

- Prefer small, focused edits that keep the existing structure intact.
- Record useful implementation notes, verification details, and follow-up context in the relevant ishoo before marking it complete.
- Run the project validation loop after changes and fix failures before considering the work done.
